rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
An Olympic athlete is a person who has competed in any of the events organized and endorsed by the International Olympic Committee.
Things that are olympic athletes:
## Those persons who were part of the Olympics either as individual competitors or as part of a team (e.g. Michael Phelps, Yael Arad, Yu-Na Kim, Manu Ginobili, Andrea Barzagli, Yelena Berezhnaya).
## Athletes who were on a national Olympic team but did not compete (e.g. Georgian luger, Nodar Kumaritashvili, died a day before the 2010 Winter Olympics competition).
Things that are NOT olympic athletes:
## Animals that were part of any Olympic competition (e.g. Big Ben, In Style).
## Coaches who have coached Olympic competitors but have not competed in the Olympic games themselves (e.g. Mick Haley, Vittorio Pozzo, Bela Karolyi).
##College athletes who have not competed in the any of the Olympic games. (e.g. Kyle Singler, Vincent Brown).
## Athletes in Olympic style competitions such as Paralympics, Special Olympics, Deaflympics, etc. (e.g. David Weir, Sarnya Parker, Oscar Pistorius). Use mso:sports.tournament_event_competitor in these cases.
## Athletes who have not competed in the any of the Olympic games. (e.g. Emilio Butragueno, Adrian Peterson).
## Olympic teams (e.g. United States National Basketball Team, Brazil Olympic Football Team).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympic Athlete

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the type of medal, e.g. gold, silver or bronze, won in the particular sport for the given country/games. Note that when no value is entered for this property, mso:olympics.medals_by_sport.number_of_medals is understood to give the total number of medals won in the given sport for the given instance of mso:olympics.country_games_relationship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Medal

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of medals won in the particular sport for the given country/games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Medals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the sport for which medal information is given.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sport

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing sports records for olympic events.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympics Record

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: At which event is the record set
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Event Competition
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use sports.record.event_competition instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:sports.record.event_competition ]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: who set the record
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Record Holder
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use sports.record.record_holder instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:sports.record.record_holder]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The value of the record
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Record Result
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use sports.record.result instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:sports.record.result ]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The unit of the record: second, meter, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Record Result Unit
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use sports.record.result_unit instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:sports.record.result_unit]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all countries that have participated in the Olympic Games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Participating Country

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:olympics.participating_country to the mso:olympics.athlete(s) that represented the country in an Olympic game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Athletes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a country that participated in an Olympic game to information about the number of athletes that the country sent, the results of the events where it competed, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Country Games Relationships

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:olympics.participating_country to the mso:olympics.demonstration_medal_honor(s) the country has been awarded.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Demonstration Medals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:olympics.participating_country to the mso:olympics.games in which the country has competed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Games

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:olympics.participating_country to its IOC code.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: IOC Code

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:olympics.participating_country to the mso:olympics.medal_honor(s) awarded to the country.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Medals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all sports contested in the Olympic Games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympic Sport

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:olympics.sport to the mso:olympics.athlete_affiliation entities collecting the data for athletes competing in this sport in Olympic games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Athletes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:olympics.sport to the mso:olympics.event types in the Olympics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Events

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:olympics.sport to the mso:olympics.games in which the sport had demonstration competitions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Demonstrations in

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:olympics.sport to the mso:olympics.games in which the sport was an official competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Official Sport in

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that stores information about the number of people in each gender that participated in specific sports for countries at a particular Olympics game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sports Gender Participation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the gender for which participation information is provided in the context of the given country/games combination. Note that when no value is entered for this property, the property mso:olympics.sports_gender_participation.number_of_participants is understood to give the total number of athletes in the given sport for the given instance of mso:olympics.country_games_relationship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gender

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of athletes of the given gender that took part in the games on behalf of the country.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Participants

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the sport for which gender participation information is provided in the context of the given country/games combination.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sport

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A sports team that competes in an olympic game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympic Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:olympics.team to an instance of mso:olympics.medal_honor, which collects data on events in which the team competed in an instance of mso:olympics.games
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympic Medal Honors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all parts of the Olympic torch relays done by a given individual. Data on this type include the date the individual participated in the relay and the location the individual carried the torch through.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympic Torch Relay

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:olympics.torch_relay to the age of the bearer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Age

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:olympics.torch_relay to the date the bearer carried the torch.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:olympics.torch_relay to the mso:olympics.torch_relay_location the bearer carried the torch. Note this expected type of mso:olympics.torch_relay_location is deprecated and will be replaced with mso:location.location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:olympics.torch_relay to its mso:olympics.games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:olympics.torch_relay entity to the mso:olympics.torchbearer for the leg. The expected type of this property should eventually be changed to mso:people.person.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Torchbearer
Olympic torch relay location
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Not needed; use mso:location.location instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\jcoop] Successor:[mso:location.location]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The Olympic Games in which the torch relay passed through this place, and the torchbearer or torchbearers who carried it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympics
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If needed, this property should be added to location.location. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:location.location]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all people that have carried the Olympic torch in the ceremonial relay to start an instance of mso:olympics.games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympic Torchbearer
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. Use people.person instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:people.person]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:olympics.torchbearer to the mso:olympics.torch_relay entities in which the person carried the torch.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Participation in Relays
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. If this property is needed, it should be added to people.person. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all olympic venues. These are the sports facilities that have hosted Olympic competitions as part of a given Olympic game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympic Venue

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:olympics.venue to the mso:olympics.event_competition(s) held here.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympic Events

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:olympics.venue to the mso:olympics.games that held some competitions at the venue.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympic Games
